Setting up to build packages with pacman
Create a new user by adding the following to /etc/passwd:

tester:x:1000:999:tester:/home/tester:/bin/bash

Where 999 is the ID of the users group. Check /etc/group for the correct ID, or if users is not present in that file, add the following to it.

users:x:999:

Create a home directory:

mkdir -v /home/tester
chown -Rv tester:users /home/tester

Exit your current chroot, then chroot into your new user (make sure 1000, 999 and tester are set to the proper values for your system):

chroot --userspec=1000:999 "$CMLFS" /llvmtools/bin/env -i \
    HOME=/home/tester \
    TERM="$TERM" \
    PS1='(cmlfs chroot) [\u@\h \W]\$ ' \
    PATH=/root/.bin:/usr/bin:/usr/sbin:/bin:/sbin:/llvmtools/bin \
    /llvmtools/bin/bash --login +h
    